    "RL-based agents use reinforcement learning to learn and optimize strategies through environment interaction, with the aim of maximizing accumulated rewards.",
    "These agents are effective in environments with clear objectives such as instruction following [75,124] or building world model [108,140], where they adapt through trial and error.",
    "In contrast, LLM-based agents rely on large-language models [92,173,195].",
    "They excel in natural language processing tasks, leveraging vast textual data to master language complexities for effective communication and information retrieval.",
    "Each type of agent has distinct capabilities to achieve specific computational tasks and objectives."
